<DocsLayout title="Supersets & the rest timer" description="Group-aware rest, two ways to build supersets, and a timer that survives reloads and rings on the lock screen.">
  <SectionHero section="training" />
  <h1>Supersets &amp; the rest timer</h1>
  <DocsMeta />

  <h2>The rest timer</h2>
  <p>
    Checking off a set starts the timer automatically — per-exercise override or your account
    default, ±15 s nudges, skippable, with optional sound and vibration. It survives page
    reloads and follows you across tabs. Hosted over HTTPS, it also alerts on the phone lock
    screen, which is where you are actually looking between sets.
  </p>

  <h2>Supersets</h2>
  <p>
    A superset chains an exercise with the next one in the workout. Rest behaves the way
    supersets are meant to work: no timer between the paired exercises, one full rest after
    the group's last set. Cards wear an A/B group badge so you can see the pairing at a glance.
  </p>
  <p>Two ways to build one:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>In the picker</strong> — <em>Add superset</em> in the add-exercise sheet asks for
      two exercises and adds them pre-linked. Dismissing halfway simply leaves the first pick
      as a normal exercise.</li>
    <li><strong>From the card menu</strong> — <em>Superset with next</em> links any exercise with
      the one below it (drag them adjacent first). Same menu unlinks.</li>
  </ul>

  <Callout variant="tip" title="Routines remember pairings">
    The routine editor has the same link toggle per exercise — templates start their workouts
    with supersets already wired.
  </Callout>
</DocsLayout>
